repository-code: "https://github.com/kubasuchy/EYE-LEAN"
url: "https://github.com/kubasuchy/EYE-LEAN"
abstract: >
  Eye_lean is a Unity + Python toolkit for collecting and analyzing
  eye-tracking data from VR head-mounted displays. It ships a
  calibrator with per-user profile correction, a deterministic-replay
  system that reproduces recordings frame-accurately, a real-time
  cognitive-load monitor (RIPA2), and a researcher template
  (Skeleton) for building custom VR behavioral experiments.
keywords:
  - "eye tracking"
  - "virtual reality"
  - pupillometry
  - "cognitive load"
  - RIPA
  - LHIPA
  - "behavioral research"
  - VIVE
  - OpenXR
  - Unity
